Pattern: Airdrop reflex loop
Participants optimize for point farming or one off rewards instead of durable protocol usage.
Observed in: Consumer crypto apps, incentive launch chains, points to token programs.
Behavior: Activity spikes around reward windows, then falls off hard once emissions or speculation fades.
Risk impl: Growth metrics become misleading because they measure extraction behavior, not adoption.
Frequency: high

Pattern: Yield masking product market fit
Subsidies hide the fact that demand disappears when incentives are removed.
Observed in: DeFi liquidity programs, restaking style incentive layers, liquidity bootstrapping protocols.
Behavior: TVL and volume look strong during emissions, then collapse when the subsidy ends.
Risk impl: The protocol confuses liquidity rental with true economic demand.
Frequency: high

Pattern: Reward inversion
Users who create long term value are paid less than the users who game short term metrics.
Observed in: Points systems, social protocols, marketplace incentive schemes.
Behavior: High frequency, low quality actions get rewarded more cleanly than slower, higher value contributions.
Risk impl: The system trains participants to behave against the protocol’s real objectives.
Frequency: medium

Pattern: Emissions dependency trap
The protocol cannot remove incentives without breaking the activity it created.
Observed in: Token launch chains, liquidity mining protocols, growth stage governance systems.
Behavior: Every attempt to reduce rewards triggers complaints, activity drop-off, or governance resistance.
Risk impl: The protocol becomes locked into subsidizing its own illusion of health.
Frequency: high
